## Risks & Mitigation

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|--------|------------|
| Halo2 WASM compilation fails for browser | Medium | High | Use `wasm-pack` with `wasm-bindgen`. Pre-test wasm32-unknown-unknown target. |
| Soroban has no ZK verifier for Halo2 proofs | High | Critical | Fall back to Groth16 (one final proof instead of recursive). Or deploy verifier on Ethereum L1 and use as oracle. |
| Nova folding integration harder than expected | Medium | High | Use icicle (NVIDIA GPU acceleration) or check if existing Nova impl works with our curves |
| Stellar RPC event retention (7 days) blocks recovery | Low | Medium | Document limitation; POC can use a centralized observer |
| WASM prover too slow for <100ms target | Medium | Medium | 100ms is aspirational; accept 500ms for POC |

## Resources Needed

- Rust with `halo2` + `halo2wrong` + `nova` crates (check versions)
- `wasm-pack` for WASM compilation
- Stellar testnet account with XLM for gas
- Soroban CLI for contract deployment
- Halo2 proving keys (trusted setup if needed — depends on scheme)
- Existing `contracts/pool/` as reference for token bridge
